`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- FPS tracking via exponential moving average (`ema = 0.9 * ema + 0.1 * fps`) is more stable than a rolling window — a window requires allocating an array; EMA uses a single float.
- `performance.memory` is a non-standard Chrome extension (available in React Native via JSC/Hermes's Performance API). We guard with an optional-chain so it doesn't crash on environments that don't expose it.
- Exporting pure functions instead of a class makes these trivially testable without mocks.
