`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `import * as THREE` → named import conversion uses Python's `re.sub(r'THREE\.([A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*)', r'\1', content)`. This is safe because all three.js public exports start with uppercase — the pattern only matches those identifiers.
- `dpr={1}` on the R3F `<Canvas>` is the correct lever (not setting `gl.pixelRatio` imperatively). R3F reads `dpr` before creating the WebGL context, so it prevents the extra framebuffer allocation on high-DPI screens entirely.
- The `PerspectiveCamera` collision pattern (drei exports a React component, three exports the raw class with the same name) is a recurring gotcha. The fix is `import type { PerspectiveCamera as PerspectiveCameraImpl } from "three"` — it imports the type only (no runtime value conflict) under a different name.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

